
@startuml

' Classes
class Doctor {
  - practitionerNumber: String
  - fullName: String
  - address: String
  - phone: String
  - signature: Image
}

class Patient {
  - healthNumber: String
  - firstName: String
  - lastName: String
  - dateOfBirth: Date
  - address: String
  - phone: String
}

class Lab {
  - name: String
  - registrationNumber: String
  - address: String
  - businessHours: Map<Date, [TimeRange]>
  - changeCancellationFee: Double
}

class Requisition {
  - validityDate: Date
  - doctor: Doctor (1)
  - patient: Patient (1)
  - tests: List<Test> (*)
  - repetitionPattern: RepetitionPattern (0..1)
}

class Test {
  - name: String
  - duration: Duration
  - testGroup: TestGroup (1)
  - isWalkInOnly: Boolean
  - requiresSample: Boolean
}

class TestGroup {
  - groupName: String
  - type: String (e.g., "Blood", "Ultrasound")
}

class RepetitionPattern {
  - interval: String (Weekly, Monthly, EveryHalfYear, Yearly)
  - numberOfRepetitions: Integer
}

class Appointment {
  - confirmationNumber: String
  - date: Date
  - startTime: Time
  - endTime: Time
  - lab: Lab (1)
  - requisition: Requisition (1)
}

class Result {
  - test: Test (1)
  - resultType: String (Positive/Negative)
  - report: String
}

class TimeRange {
  - start: Time
  - end: Time
}

class Duration {
  - hours: Integer
  - minutes: Integer
}

' Associations and Relationships
Doctor "1" -- "1" Requisition : creates
Doctor "1" -- "many" Test : prescribes
Patient "1" -- "1" Requisition : assigned to
Patient "1" -- "many" Appointment : makes
Lab "1" -- "many" Appointment : hosts
Test "1" -- "1" TestGroup : belongs to
Test "1" -- "0..1" RepetitionPattern : has
Test "1" -- "1" Duration : has
Test "1" -- "1" Result : has
Requisition "1" -- "0..1" RepetitionPattern : has
Requisition "1" -- "1" Appointment : leads to (if appointment required)

' Constraints
note right of Doctor
  Cannot prescribe tests for themselves.
end note

note right of Test
  Can be combined only with other tests in the same group.
end note

note right of Appointment
  Only one appointment per repeated requisition at a time.
  Change/cancellation within 24h incurs a fee.
end note

@enduml

---

### ✅ Diagram Highlights:

- **Doctor**: Creates requisitions and prescribes tests. Must have valid credentials.
- **Patient**: Has a requisition assigned and can book appointments.
- **Lab**: Offers tests and schedules appointments with fixed business hours.
- **Test**: Defined by type, group, and duration. May require sample or walk-in.
- **Requisition**: Links a doctor and a patient with multiple tests from the same group.
- **Appointment**: Made by a patient at a lab for a specific test or set of tests.
- **TestGroup**: Enforces grouping logic (e.g., all blood tests must be in one group).
- **Result**: Captures test outcomes and reports.

